🧠 1. Core / Built-in Python Libraries

These come with Python itself (no install needed)

math → mathematical functions
datetime → date and time
os → file and system operations
sys → system-level stuff
random → random numbers
re → regular expressions

👉 Use these first if you are beginner

📊 2. Data Science & Machine Learning

Very important for your ML subject

NumPy → arrays and math
Pandas → data handling
Matplotlib → graphs
Seaborn → advanced graphs
Scikit-learn → ML models

Advanced:

TensorFlow
PyTorch
🌐 3. Web Development Frameworks

For your chatbot / projects

Backend frameworks:
Django → full powerful framework
Flask → simple and beginner-friendly
FastAPI → very fast APIs

👉 For your projects:

Flask = easy start
FastAPI = best for APIs + AI apps
